### 1. List all birds — empty database (200, meta.count: 0)
GET http://localhost:8787/api/birds

###

### 2. Create a bird (201)
POST http://localhost:8787/api/birds
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "common_name": "Great Kiskadee",
  "scientific_name": "Pitangus sulphuratus",
  "family": "Tyrannidae",
  "description": "A large, boldly marked flycatcher with a booming call."
}

###

### 3. Get bird by id (200) — use the id returned in #2
GET http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1

###

### 4. Patch bird — update description (200)
PATCH http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Common in South Texas and Latin America."
}

###

### 5. Create a bird — missing common_name (422)
POST http://localhost:8787/api/birds
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "scientific_name": "Ortalis vetula"
}

###

### 6. Create a sighting for bird 1 (201)
POST http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1/sightings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Morning survey - Resaca trail",
  "description": "Pair observed foraging near water.",
  "status": "logged"
}

###

### 7. Create a sighting with defaults only (201) — status defaults to planned, description to ""
POST http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1/sightings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Follow-up count"
}

###

### 8. Create sighting — invalid status (422)
POST http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1/sightings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Bad status test",
  "status": "done"
}

###

### 9. List sightings for bird 1 (200, meta.count: 2)
GET http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1/sightings

###

### 10. Get sighting by id (200) — use the id returned in #6
GET http://localhost:8787/api/sightings/1

###

### 11. Patch sighting — update status (200)
PATCH http://localhost:8787/api/sightings/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in-field"
}

###

### 12. Patch sighting — empty body (422)
PATCH http://localhost:8787/api/sightings/1
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 13. Delete sighting 2 (204)
DELETE http://localhost:8787/api/sightings/2

###

### 14. Delete sighting 2 again — not found (404)
DELETE http://localhost:8787/api/sightings/2

###

### 15. List bird 1 sightings — count drops to 1 (200)
GET http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1/sightings

###

### 16. Delete bird 1 — D1 cascade removes its sightings (204)
DELETE http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1

###

### 17. Confirm bird is gone (404)
GET http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1

###

### 18. Confirm no orphaned sightings — bird route returns 404 (not empty list)
GET http://localhost:8787/api/birds/1/sightings